a = sns.heatmap(corr,mask=mask, annot=True, fmt='.2f')

roty = a.set_yticklabels(a.get_yticklabels(), rotation=30)

Observations from pairplots and heatmap:¶

  1. Cement has strong correlation with strength
  2. Slag,ash, coarseagg and fineagg are weak predictors
  3. Water appears to have a negative correlation with strength
  4. Superplastic and Age have positive correlation with strength

In [521]:
def PrintMetrics(name,model, predicted):
    algo_names.append(name)
    trainScoreValue = model.score(x_train,y_train)
    train_scores.append(trainScoreValue)
    print(name, " Training Score = ",trainScoreValue)
    testScoreValue = model.score(x_test,y_test)
    test_scores.append(testScoreValue)
    print(name, " Test Score = ", testScoreValue)
    r2Value = r2_score(y_test, predicted)
    r2_scores.append(r2Value)
    print(name, " R2 Score = ", r2Value)
In [522]:
def PrintScaledMetrics(name,model, predicted):
    trainScoreValue = model.score(scaled_x_train,y_train)
    print(name, " Training Score = ",trainScoreValue)
    testScoreValue = model.score(scaled_x_test,y_test)
    print(name, " Test Score = ", testScoreValue)
    r2Value = r2_score(y_test, predicted)
    print(name, " R2 Score = ", r2Value)
